#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:3
msgid "Curriculum Advisory Committee Invitation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:5
msgid ""
"Subject: Invitation to Join the [ carpentry org ] [ lesson title ] "
"Curriculum Advisory Committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:7
msgid "Dear [ name ],"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:9
msgid ""
"Thank you for your interest in being a member of the [ carpentry org ] [ "
"lesson title ] Curriculum Advisory Committee! Because of your experience "
"working with [ relevant data types ] and your perspective on and commitment "
"to teaching [ lesson title ] data skills, we would like to invite you to be "
"a member of this committee. We think you bring important and unique insight "
"to what skills should be taught to [ lesson title ] researchers as well as "
"how they should be taught."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:12
msgid ""
"The [ carpentry org ] [ lesson title ] curriculum aims to teach the core "
"skills and perspectives for working effectively and reproducibly with [ "
"lesson title ] data. The role of the [ carpentry org ] [ lesson title ] "
"Curriculum Advisory Committee is to provide the oversight, vision and "
"leadership for the [ lesson title ] curriculum as a whole."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:14
msgid "This Committee will meet bi-annually to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:16
msgid ""
"Discuss curricular updates that have been proposed by Instructors, "
"Maintainers or other community members."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:17
msgid ""
"Provide recommendations for other potential updates based on current "
"approaches in the field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:18
msgid ""
"Discuss proposals for new lesson ideas and provide recommendations about "
"whether they should be developed or accepted and whether they should be "
"incorporated into existing workshop curriculum or as standalone lessons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:19
msgid ""
"Provide a written report of the meeting regarding decisions around "
"curriculum updates and recommendations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:21
msgid "Additionally Committee members are expected to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:22
msgid ""
"Be familiar with [ carpentry org ] [ lesson title ] lesson content and "
"respond to content-related issues on individual lessons as needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:23
msgid ""
"Act as Maintainers for the '[ lesson title ] workshop' repository, making "
"sure it’s up to date with the overall goals of the workshops and correct "
"links to curriculum and update as needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:25
msgid "Prior to lesson release (currently on a 6 month schedule):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:26
msgid ""
"Review individual lessons to make sure curriculum-level learning objectives "
"are being met by the set of lessons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:27
msgid ""
"Prepare the ‘[ lesson title ] workshop’ repository for release. Will be "
"Editors for this repository at release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:29
msgid ""
"Please let me know if you are still interested in serving on the [ lesson "
"title ] Curriculum Advisory Committee and can commit to these "
"responsibilities. If you have any questions before you can accept this role,"
" please also let me know."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:31
msgid "Thanks so much. We look forward to the opportunity to work with you!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:33
msgid "Best,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:35
msgid "[ sender name ]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:37
msgid "Initiate Scheduling of First Meeting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:39
msgid ""
"Subject: Scheduling First Meeting of the [ carpentry org ] [ lesson title ] "
"Curriculum Advisory Committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:41
msgid "Hi everyone,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:43
msgid ""
"Thank you to those who so far have confirmed your interest in being a part "
"of the committee. I'd like to get us started on setting up our first bi-"
"annual meeting. This meeting will be between [date] and [date], in advance "
"of the [upcoming Bug BBQ or lesson release] which will be held [dates]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:45
msgid ""
"At our first meeting, we will be making decisions about some core proposed "
"revisions to the existing [lesson title] lessons. The developers and "
"Maintainers of the lessons will be providing that list, along with relevant "
"background information, for people to look over in preparation for the "
"meeting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:47
msgid ""
"To help schedule the meeting, could everyone please add their availability "
"to this [whenisgood](link to whenisgood poll) by this coming Friday "
"[(date)]? Please make sure to put in your time zone at the top of the poll. "
"I'll look at the results and let everyone know the meeting time by [date] so"
" that you can clear up any holds on your calendar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:49
msgid ""
"Please let me know if you have any questions in advance of our first meeting"
" in a few weeks. I'm looking forward to meeting everyone soon!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:51
#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:69
#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/lesson_development/email_templates.md:86
msgid "Best, [ sender name ]"
msgstr ""

